gov.usgs.earthquake.quakewatch

Class EIDSListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • CubeClient
      • gov.usgs.earthquake.quakewatch.EIDSListener

  • public class EIDSListener
extends CubeClient
    Accept Cube messages and if the mag >= 3.5 and network for solutin is US, create fetch list. This class is likely obsolete as PDL has replaced EIDS as a source of earthquake data.
    If it is smaller than 3.5 and the network is one of US,NC,BK,CI,NM,AK,AT,PT,PR,UU,LD, or UW, create a fetchlist. Ignore all other events. Use FetchListBuilder class to analyze stations and computer distances, etc. to apply the algorithm.

      • EIDSListener

        public EIDSListener(java.lang.String[] args,
                    java.lang.String nets,
                    FetchListBuilder f,
                    StrongMotionBuilder sm)
             throws TauModelException
        create the EIDS listen which will use FetchListBuilder and StrongMotionBuilder to create entries in the fetchlist and PGM tables.
        Parameters:
        args - Are not used by EIDSListener but are pasted to CubeClient
        nets - The list of nets allowed to declare events for processing, all run together like USNCCI...
        f - The fetchlist builder to use to process events and create fetchlist entries for SM data
        sm - The strong motion builder to use to build PGM and PGMRESULTS entry for computations of PGM
        Throws:
        TauModelException - If one were to be thrown
